The All Progressives Congress (APC) has defeated the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) at the two polling units located in the presidential villa. The villa polling units — 021 and 022 — are located in Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC). The villa is located in the Asokoro district and houses President Muhammadu Buhari. At polling unit 021, the ruling party clinched 84 votes to defeat the opposition party which secured 30 votes for the councillorship election. For the chairmanship at the same polling unit, the APC polled 79 votes to win PDP that secured 36. At polling unit 022, APC polled 41 votes, while the PDP secured 33 in the chairmanship contest. For the councillorship contest in the same polling unit, APC won the contest after securing 45 votes to defeat the PDP which got 30. Still within the presidential villa, while no one turned up to vote at polling unit 120, only one person voted at 121. The person voted for PDP for both councillorship and chairmanship polls.